1453
01:22:40,550 --> 01:22:42,750
I'll do my best to try and distract them.

1454
01:22:42,780 --> 01:22:45,150
You steal the shells while they're not looking.

1455
01:22:45,180 --> 01:22:46,020
- Huh?

1456
01:22:49,020 --> 01:22:50,160
- There he is!

1457
01:22:50,190 --> 01:22:51,620
Perhaps I, huh?

1458
01:22:55,560 --> 01:22:57,360
It seems I have a colleague.

1459
01:22:57,400 --> 01:23:00,930
It's quite odd for a fly to be that interested in a carrot.

1460
01:23:02,000 --> 01:23:03,400
Colleague?

1461
01:23:03,440 --> 01:23:05,740
I've almost turned into a proper fly.

1462
01:23:07,210 --> 01:23:08,410
Hm?

1463
01:23:08,440 --> 01:23:10,080
I should have known this would happen.

1464
01:23:10,110 --> 01:23:12,740
The momentum anchor has become an issue.

1465
01:23:27,290 --> 01:23:29,900
(somber music)

1466
01:23:35,030 --> 01:23:36,470
(engine chugging)

1467
01:23:36,500 --> 01:23:38,170
- Hey, what are you doing?

1468
01:23:46,450 --> 01:23:47,810
Wait, now?

1469
01:23:47,850 --> 01:23:49,380
But the plan was to blast the well

1470
01:23:49,410 --> 01:23:51,520
in front of everyone tomorrow!

1471
01:23:51,550 --> 01:23:52,950
Are you listening?

1472
01:23:53,950 --> 01:23:56,560
- You don't understand me at all, do you?

1473
01:23:56,590 --> 01:23:58,120
- You're right, I don't!

1474
01:23:58,160 --> 01:23:59,190
That's why I-

1475
01:24:00,160 --> 01:24:02,090
- You're just a poor excusable wizard.

1476
01:24:04,200 --> 01:24:08,200
All you were able to do is change me into a hideous monster.

1477
01:24:08,230 --> 01:24:09,230
- I'm sorry.

1478
01:24:12,300 --> 01:24:13,410
I tried my best!

1479
01:24:13,440 --> 01:24:15,440
You know that, don't you?

1480
01:24:15,470 --> 01:24:17,510
I wanted you to be happy!

1481
01:24:17,540 --> 01:24:19,540
I didn't want the prince to hate me!

1482
01:24:19,580 --> 01:24:20,680
- [Both] Huh?

1483
01:24:22,580 --> 01:24:25,350
(somber music)

1484
01:24:27,150 --> 01:24:29,590
- [Prince] Hey you, do something!

1485
01:24:29,620 --> 01:24:31,420
You're a wizard, aren't you?

1486
01:24:31,460 --> 01:24:32,290
- Yeah, but-

1487
01:24:33,660 --> 01:24:35,490
- [Prince] If you are able to make me talk in this form,

1488
01:24:35,530 --> 01:24:38,600
then you should be able to change me back!

1489
01:24:38,630 --> 01:24:39,770
So, do it!

1490
01:24:41,530 --> 01:24:42,630
(tinkles)

1491
01:24:42,670 --> 01:24:43,740
- Ah!

1492
01:24:43,770 --> 01:24:48,470
(tinkling)(grunting)

1493
01:25:04,620 --> 01:25:06,190
- I am not the prince!

1494
01:25:06,220 --> 01:25:07,760
I am Zan Gu now!

1495
01:25:16,840 --> 01:25:19,270
- I'm pretty sure that Master Kamadoma

1496
01:25:19,300 --> 01:25:21,210
will be waking up soon.

1497
01:25:21,240 --> 01:25:22,670
He's gonna be mad.

1498
01:25:22,710 --> 01:25:25,140
- Then we'll have to destroy Kamadoma too.

1499
01:25:25,180 --> 01:25:28,110
- What? That's not even possible!

1500
01:25:31,850 --> 01:25:33,320
- Stop, Zan Gu!

1501
01:25:34,020 --> 01:25:38,990
(grunting) (tense music)

1502
01:25:48,830 --> 01:25:50,670
It's important to you, right?

1503
01:25:50,700 --> 01:25:52,370
Please, don't destroy it.

1504
01:25:52,400 --> 01:25:53,440
- What do you know?

1505
01:25:53,470 --> 01:25:54,340
- If the water doesn't flow,

1506
01:25:54,370 --> 01:25:56,880
this entire world is gonna dry up soon.

1507
01:25:56,910 --> 01:25:58,110
- It's not your business!

1508
01:25:58,140 --> 01:26:00,310
Nobody asked you so shut up, will you?

1509
01:26:01,710 --> 01:26:04,920
- Ron, long time no see.

1510
01:26:04,950 --> 01:26:06,590
- What are you talking about?

1511
01:26:06,620 --> 01:26:08,920
I don't know anybody with that name.

1512
01:26:08,950 --> 01:26:11,320
- You don't need to pretend anymore.

1513
01:26:11,360 --> 01:26:13,690
If the timeless rain well is destroyed,

1514
01:26:13,730 --> 01:26:15,390
there'll be consequences.

1515
01:26:15,430 --> 01:26:16,700
(melancholic music)

1516
01:26:16,730 --> 01:26:18,760
The forest where we grew up and went to school

1517
01:26:18,800 --> 01:26:20,570
will eventually die.

1518
01:26:20,600 --> 01:26:22,200
And all our families and friends

1519
01:26:22,230 --> 01:26:24,240
will be in despair because of it.

1520
01:26:24,270 --> 01:26:25,240
- So what?

1521
01:26:25,270 --> 01:26:26,940
Don't talk to me like we're friends.

1522
01:26:27,640 --> 01:26:29,510
- But we are, aren't we, Ron?

1523
01:26:35,050 --> 01:26:38,420
(Hippocrates sobbing)

1524
01:26:41,020 --> 01:26:43,690
- Look at that, it seems the prince and Ron

1525
01:26:43,720 --> 01:26:44,860
are closer than we thought.

1526
01:26:44,890 --> 01:26:46,020
- Are you certain?

1527
01:26:46,060 --> 01:26:48,190
- I'll go get them immediately.

1528
01:26:48,230 --> 01:26:50,560
- No, the prince needs to decide

1529
01:26:50,600 --> 01:26:52,760
if he wants to come back or not.

1530
01:26:52,800 --> 01:26:55,830
However, I should still break the spell on them.

1531
01:26:57,840 --> 01:26:59,540
- Shut up, shut up, shut up!

1532
01:26:59,570 --> 01:27:02,470
Stop pretending like you know everything, you will twerp!

1533
01:27:02,510 --> 01:27:04,310
(zaps)

1534
01:27:04,340 --> 01:27:05,680
- Ron!

1535
01:27:05,710 --> 01:27:07,180
(zaps)

1536
01:27:07,210 --> 01:27:08,610
- Huh?

1537
01:27:08,650 --> 01:27:10,680
(energetic music)

1538
01:27:10,720 --> 01:27:12,150
- Mr. Hippocrates!

1539
01:27:12,180 --> 01:27:13,020
- Akane!

1540
01:27:16,820 --> 01:27:18,090
- Master Hippocrates!

1541
01:27:19,790 --> 01:27:20,790
(zaps)

1542
01:27:20,830 --> 01:27:21,760
(gasps)

1543
01:27:21,790 --> 01:27:24,030
(neighing)

1544
01:27:25,330 --> 01:27:26,400
- Over here!

1545
01:27:26,430 --> 01:27:27,500
It's safer.

1546
01:27:27,530 --> 01:27:28,700
Pipo, the carrot!

1547
01:27:28,730 --> 01:27:30,470
- Right!

1548
01:27:30,500 --> 01:27:31,340
Ron.

1549
01:27:32,740 --> 01:27:33,970
Ron!

1550
01:27:35,510 --> 01:27:37,880
(yelling)

1551
01:27:39,310 --> 01:27:40,680
To the exit!

1552
01:27:40,710 --> 01:27:43,320
(whimpering)

1553
01:27:46,280 --> 01:27:46,890
(neighing)

1554
01:27:46,920 --> 01:27:48,350
(yelling)

1555
01:27:48,390 --> 01:27:49,790
(slaps)

1556
01:27:49,820 --> 01:27:51,820
(neighing)

1557
01:27:51,860 --> 01:27:54,890
(energetic music)

1558
01:27:56,800 --> 01:27:57,600
(grunts)

1559
01:27:57,630 --> 01:27:59,200
Master Hippocrates!

1560
01:28:17,650 --> 01:28:18,750
- Please, turn around.

1561
01:28:18,780 --> 01:28:20,120
I want out.

1562
01:28:20,150 --> 01:28:21,950
- Just try and stop me.

1563
01:28:23,890 --> 01:28:26,260
If you're truly the Goddess of the Green Wind,

1564
01:28:26,290 --> 01:28:27,690
then stop me.

1565
01:28:27,730 --> 01:28:30,530
(somber music)

1566
01:28:37,640 --> 01:28:40,110
(grunting)

1567
01:28:52,450 --> 01:28:54,290
Those bugs are scared.

1568
01:28:54,320 --> 01:28:56,720
They're nothing, completely insignificant.

1569
01:28:57,890 --> 01:28:59,660
And you are the same.

1570
01:29:02,960 --> 01:29:06,000
(somber music)

1571
01:29:06,030 --> 01:29:07,070
- Stop it!

1572
01:29:16,910 --> 01:29:18,880
- We all die eventually.

1573
01:29:18,910 --> 01:29:20,080
- But even so!

1574
01:29:21,910 --> 01:29:23,520
- Better hold on.

1575
01:29:23,550 --> 01:29:25,220
Here comes the wall.

1576
01:29:29,920 --> 01:29:32,320
(crashing)

1577
01:29:32,360 --> 01:29:34,760
(whimpering)

1578
01:29:45,670 --> 01:29:48,670
(people exclaiming)

1579
01:29:53,910 --> 01:29:56,510
(crashing)

1580
01:29:56,550 --> 01:29:59,220
(ominous music)

1581
01:30:30,650 --> 01:30:31,480
Move.

1582
01:30:32,750 --> 01:30:33,650
- Do not do this, Zan Gu.

1583
01:30:33,690 --> 01:30:35,520
You're making a massive mistake!

1584
01:30:36,790 --> 01:30:39,460
(ominous music)

1585
01:30:51,000 --> 01:30:52,140
- [Captain] First platoon up the stairs.

1586
01:30:52,170 --> 01:30:54,210
Everyone else, hold!

1587
01:30:57,310 --> 01:30:58,840
- You were afraid, right?

1588
01:31:03,010 --> 01:31:05,580
You were scared of it, rhe ceremony.

1589
01:31:08,720 --> 01:31:11,060
It had been decided for you when you were born.

1590
01:31:11,090 --> 01:31:14,230
But still, you didn't wanna do it, huh?

1591
01:31:15,990 --> 01:31:18,200
- Three generations of men before me

1592
01:31:18,230 --> 01:31:21,100
succeeded at their drop mist ceremonies.

1593
01:31:22,770 --> 01:31:24,570
(melancholic music)

1594
01:31:24,600 --> 01:31:28,240
I knew that one day, it would be my turn to perform it.

1595
01:31:45,320 --> 01:31:50,500
But as I got older, my defiance suddenly began to grow.

1596
01:31:51,460 --> 01:31:53,500
After my parents died in succession,

1597
01:31:53,530 --> 01:31:55,830
I would sometimes sneak out of the castle

1598
01:31:55,870 --> 01:31:57,540
and head over Nibi.

1599
01:31:57,570 --> 01:32:00,000
One day, I ran into some delinquents

1600
01:32:00,040 --> 01:32:02,270
who robbed me of my belongings.

1601
01:32:03,810 --> 01:32:06,980
As the drop mist ceremony quickly approached,

1602
01:32:07,010 --> 01:32:09,850
my fear and anger only increased.

1603
01:32:11,120 --> 01:32:13,450
Kamadoma noticed, he became worried

1604
01:32:13,490 --> 01:32:16,790
as the ceremony coincided with his deep sleep

1605
01:32:16,820 --> 01:32:19,890
so he confined me inside of a small iron doll.

1606
01:32:26,060 --> 01:32:27,700
- If you destroy that well,

1607
01:32:28,630 --> 01:32:30,270
will your fear and anger go away?

1608
01:32:35,040 --> 01:32:36,640
(light mellow music)

1609
01:32:36,670 --> 01:32:39,210
How about I help with the ceremony?

1610
01:32:42,650 --> 01:32:45,550
I mean I'm supposed to be the goddess after all.

1611
01:32:46,450 --> 01:32:48,890
Totally makes sense, doesn't it?

1612
01:32:48,920 --> 01:32:50,020
I'll help you out.

1613
01:32:50,050 --> 01:32:51,490
You'll succeed for sure.

1614
01:32:54,860 --> 01:32:57,900
You see, I've been through tons of villages and towns

1615
01:32:57,930 --> 01:32:59,460
before coming to this world.

1616
01:32:59,500 --> 01:33:01,870
So I was surprised to see how amazing it was.

1617
01:33:01,900 --> 01:33:05,470
This place, it's so beautiful and filled with color.

1618
01:33:07,410 --> 01:33:10,280
We have more advanced technology where I'm from,

1619
01:33:10,310 --> 01:33:13,380
which makes things convenient but also inconvenient.

1620
01:33:14,350 --> 01:33:16,920
I love the bright colors of the flowers here.

1621
01:33:18,150 --> 01:33:19,920
And the stars in the night sky.

1622
01:33:22,890 --> 01:33:25,220
But my world neglects all that.

1623
01:33:28,430 --> 01:33:32,800
So I'm asking you to please protect this world.

1624
01:33:32,830 --> 01:33:34,070
Only you can do it.

1625
01:33:34,100 --> 01:33:35,530
I believe in you.

1626
01:33:36,500 --> 01:33:39,100
(enchanting moving music)

1627
01:33:39,140 --> 01:33:41,340
(gasps)

1628
01:33:53,050 --> 01:33:56,420
(mellow moving music)

1629
01:34:03,090 --> 01:34:05,700
You're back to being you again.

1630
01:34:10,030 --> 01:34:12,300
(all gasp)

1631
01:34:14,470 --> 01:34:16,310
- I've finally returned.

1632
01:34:16,340 --> 01:34:19,740
- The prince is back to normal!

1633
01:34:19,780 --> 01:34:22,780
(melancholic music)

1634
01:34:56,210 --> 01:34:57,280
- [Chii] Sorry for leaving you alone.

1635
01:34:57,320 --> 01:34:58,620
Were you scared?

1636
01:34:58,650 --> 01:34:59,880
- Mm-mm.

1637
01:34:59,920 --> 01:35:02,250
Mr. Hippocrates, I've done some thinking

1638
01:35:02,290 --> 01:35:04,160
and I think we should give the prince

