01:35:04,190 --> 01:35:06,360
the momentum anchor, however,

1640
01:35:07,590 --> 01:35:10,030
I know it was really difficult to make

1641
01:35:10,060 --> 01:35:14,330
but honestly, it's done a lot for me, like give me courage.

1642
01:35:15,300 --> 01:35:17,500
I know it's possible to make another one.

1643
01:35:17,540 --> 01:35:20,770
After all, you're the best alchemist in this entire world.

1644
01:35:23,410 --> 01:35:25,280
- Well, I can only make such a precious item

1645
01:35:25,310 --> 01:35:27,180
in my laboratory.

1646
01:35:27,210 --> 01:35:29,480
(groans)

1647
01:35:31,320 --> 01:35:32,620
- [Akane] I'm sorry, Chii.

1648
01:35:33,380 --> 01:35:34,690
- It's fine, get in.

1649
01:35:39,920 --> 01:35:41,030
What's that?

1650
01:35:41,060 --> 01:35:45,200
- This is a strong fuel made from valuable dragon's dung.

1651
01:35:45,230 --> 01:35:46,760
- Dragon's dung?

1652
01:35:48,230 --> 01:35:49,770
- Time to fly.

1653
01:35:49,800 --> 01:35:52,640
(energetic music)

1654
01:36:09,250 --> 01:36:11,960
(grunts)

1655
01:36:11,990 --> 01:36:14,830
(engine whirring)

1656
01:36:20,700 --> 01:36:22,970
(clanking)

1657
01:36:35,410 --> 01:36:36,610
- [Chii] Hm?

1658
01:36:41,450 --> 01:36:43,820
(giggles)

1659
01:36:45,560 --> 01:36:47,460
- My lab is upstairs.

1660
01:36:51,700 --> 01:36:53,600
- I lit the fireplace for you.

1661
01:36:58,340 --> 01:37:00,540
(window clacking)

1662
01:37:00,570 --> 01:37:04,580
(mysterious ambient music)

1663
01:37:16,290 --> 01:37:17,520
- Keep stirring.

1664
01:37:18,320 --> 01:37:19,460
Keep it slow.

1665
01:37:20,320 --> 01:37:22,560
Now, take in the light of the moon.

1666
01:37:23,800 --> 01:37:28,100
Then say a small prayer in your mind, deep within your mind.

1667
01:37:28,130 --> 01:37:29,400
- Right.

1668
01:37:29,430 --> 01:37:32,570
(light mellow music)

1669
01:37:32,600 --> 01:37:34,010
- Master Hippocrates.

1670
01:37:42,310 --> 01:37:43,780
- Be sure to keep it steady.

1671
01:37:49,250 --> 01:37:51,360
(energetic music)

1672
01:37:51,390 --> 01:37:52,620
- Hey, I forgot to ask.

1673
01:37:52,660 --> 01:37:54,630
Where were you after the snowy town?

1674
01:37:54,660 --> 01:37:57,700
(exhaust blazing)

1675
01:38:00,970 --> 01:38:02,100
- We have arrived.

1676
01:38:09,170 --> 01:38:12,710
- Master Kamadoma, it's time to change your clothes.

1677
01:38:14,180 --> 01:38:15,110
(Kamadoma groans)

1678
01:38:15,150 --> 01:38:16,550
- Will you be all right?

1679
01:38:18,480 --> 01:38:19,450
- [Guard] Stop!

1680
01:38:19,480 --> 01:38:21,050
Master Hippocrates.

1681
01:38:23,590 --> 01:38:24,420
- Pardon me.

1682
01:38:24,460 --> 01:38:25,460
- What is it?

1683
01:38:25,490 --> 01:38:26,520
- Wait!

1684
01:38:28,260 --> 01:38:29,160
Akane.

1685
01:38:29,190 --> 01:38:31,160
- Forgive me, I'm a little late.

1686
01:38:36,400 --> 01:38:38,400
This momentum anchor's for you.

1687
01:38:38,440 --> 01:38:39,340
May I?

1688
01:38:39,370 --> 01:38:40,200
- Of course.

1689
01:38:46,540 --> 01:38:49,680
(mysterious music) (gasps)

1690
01:38:49,710 --> 01:38:51,350
- I have a matching one.

1691
01:38:51,380 --> 01:38:52,950
If you feel like you wanna run,

1692
01:38:52,980 --> 01:38:55,990
this will help you move forward in any situation.

1693
01:38:56,020 --> 01:38:58,220
It's power helped me get to the castle.

1694
01:38:59,360 --> 01:39:01,830
Also that I could meet you, see?

1695
01:39:03,530 --> 01:39:04,330
- I'll trust it.

1696
01:39:05,500 --> 01:39:08,330
- The mantle of the goddess, give it to her.

1697
01:39:08,370 --> 01:39:09,330
- [Woman] Yes, sir.

1698
01:39:09,370 --> 01:39:13,070
(mellow orchestral music)

1699
01:39:25,020 --> 01:39:26,050
- I was wondering,

1700
01:39:26,080 --> 01:39:28,750
what happens if he fails the drop mist ceremony?

1701
01:39:28,790 --> 01:39:30,390
- Then he will lose his life.

1702
01:39:30,420 --> 01:39:31,590
- Huh?

1703
01:39:31,620 --> 01:39:33,820
- But by performing that drastic sacrifice,

1704
01:39:33,860 --> 01:39:35,590
he will ensure that our world

1705
01:39:35,630 --> 01:39:38,560
will be filled as water until the next generation.

1706
01:39:38,600 --> 01:39:41,070
The royal rain family has been tied to water

1707
01:39:41,100 --> 01:39:42,370
for many, many years.

1708
01:39:42,400 --> 01:39:46,170
And as the prince, I'm sure that boy is well aware of this.

1709
01:39:47,270 --> 01:39:50,270
(suspenseful music)

1710
01:40:07,460 --> 01:40:08,460
- You're scared?

1711
01:40:08,490 --> 01:40:13,700
- Mm-mm.

1712
01:41:00,750 --> 01:41:03,180
(tinkling)

1713
01:41:19,630 --> 01:41:21,830
(sighs)

1714
01:41:23,570 --> 01:41:27,540
(spectators murmuring)

1715
01:41:27,570 --> 01:41:30,980
- Something went wrong. - What's going on?

1716
01:41:40,280 --> 01:41:42,790
(gasps)

1717
01:41:42,820 --> 01:41:45,790
(wind blowing)

1718
01:42:06,310 --> 01:42:07,240
- Hm, what?

1719
01:42:08,650 --> 01:42:10,710
- The ceremony was a failure.

1720
01:42:10,750 --> 01:42:13,580
Now, I must dedicate my body to the well.

1721
01:42:13,620 --> 01:42:14,820
Huh?

1722
01:42:14,850 --> 01:42:17,350
Wait a second, but that's so cruel!

1723
01:42:17,390 --> 01:42:19,090
Hey, tell him to stop!

1724
01:42:19,120 --> 01:42:21,130
- Are you suggesting cruel things don't happen

1725
01:42:21,160 --> 01:42:24,400
for the greater benefit of many in your world?

1726
01:42:24,430 --> 01:42:25,860
- It's fine, Akane.

1727
01:42:34,140 --> 01:42:34,970
Thank you.

1728
01:42:35,670 --> 01:42:36,910
Farewell.

1729
01:42:45,420 --> 01:42:46,250
- Akane!

1730
01:42:47,550 --> 01:42:50,220
(both grunting)

1731
01:42:57,430 --> 01:42:59,430
(creaking)

1732
01:42:59,460 --> 01:43:02,130
(swooshing)

1733
01:43:02,170 --> 01:43:04,170
(gasps)

1734
01:43:09,240 --> 01:43:11,480
(tinkling)

1735
01:43:18,580 --> 01:43:21,020
- Well done, prince, good work.

1736
01:43:22,150 --> 01:43:25,420
I saw your admirable resolution as the rain king.

1737
01:43:25,460 --> 01:43:26,460
Congratulations.

1738
01:43:28,930 --> 01:43:31,000
Show your gratitude to that girl.

1739
01:43:31,860 --> 01:43:33,760
Reward her bravery.

1740
01:43:33,800 --> 01:43:34,830
- Yes!

1741
01:43:36,200 --> 01:43:38,540
(swooshing)

1742
01:43:41,440 --> 01:43:42,240
- [Woman] They're here!

1743
01:43:42,270 --> 01:43:42,870
They're alive!

1744
01:43:42,910 --> 01:43:44,510
- [Woman] What happened?

1745
01:43:44,540 --> 01:43:46,240
- She's still alive!

1746
01:43:46,280 --> 01:43:48,880
- I won't jump again, so don't worry.

1747
01:43:49,780 --> 01:43:51,880
- [Man] How's that possible?

1748
01:43:51,920 --> 01:43:53,880
- Wait, Akane, let me go.

1749
01:43:53,920 --> 01:43:55,050
The ceremony!

1750
01:43:59,820 --> 01:44:02,890
(woman vocalizing)

1751
01:44:08,670 --> 01:44:13,140
(uplifting foreign language music)

1752
01:44:14,640 --> 01:44:17,470
(Prince grunting)

1753
01:45:02,720 --> 01:45:05,560
(people cheering)

1754
01:45:25,510 --> 01:45:27,680
(panting)

1755
01:45:31,720 --> 01:45:35,720
(mellow foreign language music)

1756
01:46:13,220 --> 01:46:14,660
- If you look on that wall,

1757
01:46:14,690 --> 01:46:18,000
you'll see the hand print of the goddess from 600 years ago.

1758
01:46:19,400 --> 01:46:22,130
(Akane grunting)

1759
01:46:24,100 --> 01:46:27,200
- Aw, and I thought we fixed it.

1760
01:46:27,240 --> 01:46:30,370
- It's strange how the goddess always seems to trip there.

1761
01:46:32,480 --> 01:46:34,850
- I should return the momentum anchor.

1762
01:46:34,880 --> 01:46:35,810
- There's no need.

1763
01:46:35,850 --> 01:46:37,250
- Huh?

1764
01:46:37,280 --> 01:46:39,020
- You haven't had the anchor for quite some time.

1765
01:46:40,520 --> 01:46:42,920
I gave you an opportunity but in the end,

1766
01:46:42,950 --> 01:46:45,490
you moved forward of your own free will.

1767
01:46:46,520 --> 01:46:48,790
- So you're admitting to being a fake then?

1768
01:46:48,830 --> 01:46:49,930
- How rude!

1769
01:46:49,960 --> 01:46:51,500
What's more important than the item

1770
01:46:51,530 --> 01:46:54,300
is that it's user possessed as a strong mind.

1771
01:46:54,330 --> 01:46:57,600
- Hm, that just sounds like a bad excuse to me.

1772
01:46:57,630 --> 01:46:58,500
Well, you ready?

1773
01:46:58,540 --> 01:46:59,870
- Uh-huh.

1774
01:46:59,900 --> 01:47:02,270
- I have a favorite ask you.

1775
01:47:03,710 --> 01:47:04,880
(giggles)

1776
01:47:04,910 --> 01:47:06,140
Muah!

1777
01:47:07,580 --> 01:47:08,410
Muah!

1778
01:47:09,680 --> 01:47:11,420
Thank you so much.

1779
01:47:11,450 --> 01:47:12,520
- No problem.

1780
01:47:13,380 --> 01:47:14,220
Muah!

1781
01:47:15,090 --> 01:47:16,550
- Master Hippocrates!

1782
01:47:16,590 --> 01:47:17,190
- Huh?

1783
01:47:17,220 --> 01:47:19,060
- Aren't you so jealous?

1784
01:47:19,090 --> 01:47:19,920
- Hardly!

1785
01:47:19,960 --> 01:47:21,790
(laughing)

1786
01:47:21,830 --> 01:47:22,730
Akane, for you.

1787
01:47:23,930 --> 01:47:25,900
This is a gift that was made for the guest

1788
01:47:25,930 --> 01:47:27,060
of the king of rain.

1789
01:47:28,830 --> 01:47:30,400
- It's beautiful, thank you.

1790
01:47:32,440 --> 01:47:33,270
- Pipo.

1791
01:47:35,640 --> 01:47:36,610
(sighs)

1792
01:47:36,640 --> 01:47:38,010
- We've been out here for three days.

1793
01:47:38,040 --> 01:47:39,780
Midori must be pretty worried about us.

1794
01:47:39,810 --> 01:47:40,810
- Yeah, you're right.

1795
01:47:40,840 --> 01:47:42,250
- You needn't worry about that.

1796
01:47:42,280 --> 01:47:43,650
Because one day in our world,

1797
01:47:43,680 --> 01:47:46,620
it's only about an hour in your world.

1798
01:47:46,650 --> 01:47:48,120
- Wait, is that true?

1799
01:47:48,150 --> 01:47:50,750
So then, next time we come here.

1800
01:47:51,760 --> 01:47:53,220
- Pipo and I will be gone.

1801
01:47:54,290 --> 01:47:57,590
This world, however, will likely not change much.

1802
01:47:57,630 --> 01:47:58,760
That much I know.

1803
01:48:01,100 --> 01:48:04,200
(mellow string music)

1804
01:48:04,230 --> 01:48:07,140
That music will guide you both home.

1805
01:48:07,170 --> 01:48:09,970
Now, go forward and move quickly.

1806
01:48:10,010 --> 01:48:11,580
Be sure to never look back.

1807
01:48:14,910 --> 01:48:16,050
- [Pipo] Take care!

1808
01:48:16,080 --> 01:48:17,250
I'll miss you!

1809
01:48:19,620 --> 01:48:22,050
- [Akane] We appreciate everything you've done for us.

1810
01:48:22,090 --> 01:48:23,120
Thank you!

1811
01:48:28,930 --> 01:48:32,530
(energetic string music)

1812
01:48:34,470 --> 01:48:36,500
- Oh, so that's where you've been.

1813
01:48:49,480 --> 01:48:51,920
- Hey, Chii, I'm going home.

1814
01:48:51,950 --> 01:48:54,280
- Yeah, sure, see you later.

1815
01:48:55,920 --> 01:48:57,220
And who might you be?

1816
01:48:58,060 --> 01:48:59,690
- I was here a few hours ago.

1817
01:48:59,720 --> 01:49:02,330
You recommended this lamp to me, remember?

1818
01:49:02,360 --> 01:49:04,800
When I used it at home, it worked like a charm.

1819
01:49:04,830 --> 01:49:07,660
So I'd really like to buy it now if that's okay.

1820
01:49:12,970 --> 01:49:15,040
Oh, you left those sitting around

1821
01:49:15,070 --> 01:49:17,070
and I figured they needed water.

1822
01:49:17,110 --> 01:49:18,240
You didn't come back right away

1823
01:49:18,280 --> 01:49:21,140
so I went and found that vase in your kitchen.

1824
01:49:21,180 --> 01:49:22,280
- You can have it.

1825
01:49:23,780 --> 01:49:26,720
Just look after my shop for a while as payment.

1826
01:49:28,920 --> 01:49:30,550
I'm taking a nap.

1827
01:49:30,590 --> 01:49:31,760
- Hey, wait.

1828
01:49:34,190 --> 01:49:36,660
- Play something that'll help me fall asleep.

1829
01:49:42,130 --> 01:49:44,700
(mellow music)

1830
01:50:04,990 --> 01:50:08,490
(mellow orchestral music)

1831
01:50:16,370 --> 01:50:18,040
- Mom, I'm home!

1832
01:50:18,070 --> 01:50:19,340
- [Midori] Welcome back.

1833
01:50:25,980 --> 01:50:27,210
- I love you, Mom.

1834
01:50:27,240 --> 01:50:30,010
Thank you for the amazing birthday present.

1835
01:50:30,050 --> 01:50:30,850
- Huh?

1836
01:50:30,880 --> 01:50:32,250
- By the way, Mom.

1837
01:50:33,420 --> 01:50:34,920
The world's huge, huh?

1838
01:50:34,950 --> 01:50:35,950
- Yes, it really is.

1839
01:50:37,120 --> 01:50:39,120
- On top of that, it's beautiful.

1840
01:50:39,160 --> 01:50:40,590
- Even more than you know.

1841
01:50:48,130 --> 01:50:51,300
(melancholic music)

1842
01:51:03,510 --> 01:51:04,720
- [Akane] It's been a long time

1843
01:51:04,750 --> 01:51:06,420
since I felt this close to my mom.

1844
01:51:08,120 --> 01:51:09,390
After all that's happened,

1845
01:51:09,420 --> 01:51:13,690
I can't help but feel like my world's expanded, maybe.

1846
